TextBody:
Hello Dominik,

Apologies for the confusion. PingCastle download should contain this file in the folder (see below). Open this file using Notepad++ or similar and edit the field for the license and add your license to it (see below). Once this is done, it should then run as the licensed version.

Also, just to clarify which version of PingCastle have you installed? You need to have the basic version installed first before upgrading it to the standard license. The basic version is the only version that will have the pingcastle.exe.config file.

(Link to the basic edition is below)

Release PingCastle 3.3.0.1 · netwrix/pingcastle · GitHub
